cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various machine learning techniques, such as insertion-based modeling and soft order-reward framework, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of generation order on translation quality, which could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) where the order of processing pixels or features can affect the output.
